Title: Series: Four landscapes with the Holy Family on their Flight into Egypt
Description: A rest on the flight into Egypt. Landscape with Joseph leading the ass to a river at centre right and two angels seated next to the Virgin at left, who is about to wrap the nude Christ Child in a shawl; from a series of four plates; proof before letters. Etching
Producer name: Print made by: Herman van Swanevelt
Curator's comments: This is one from a series of four, for comment see 1844,0425.15. This is second state, for another impression see S.2277; for an earlier states see 1868,0822.758. For a copy in reverse see F,2.233.
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts c.1450-1700 (8.II)
Acquisition notes: 1844,0425.1 to 27 cost £145 8s 6d in total. Individual prices have been entered when known.
